\f0\b\fs42 \cf2 Wild Rice and Barley Medley
\b0 \
\
2 tbsp. olive oil\
1 cup (1/2 large) onion, chopped\
1 shallot, finely chopped\
10-12 oz. cremini mushrooms, chopped\
1/4 cup wild rice\
1/4 cup brown rice\
1/2 cup pearl parley\
2 cloves garlic, finely chopped\
1 tsp. fresh thyme, finely chopped\
3 cups chicken stock\
kosher salt, to taste\
ground black pepper, to taste\
\
Directions\
\
In a deep saucepan, dutch oven or pot, heat olive oil over medium heat and then add the onions and shallots.\'a0 Cook for 5 minutes, until they start to sweat, and then add the mushrooms.\'a0 Cook until the mushrooms begin to release some of their juices, about 5-8 minutes.\
\
Add the brown rice, wild rice, barley and garlic and cook for 1 minute.\'a0\
\
Stir in the chicken stock and season to taste with kosher salt and ground black pepper.\'a0 Bring mixture to a boil.\'a0 Cover and cook, without stirring, until the liquid is absorbed, about 50-60 minutes.\'a0 Let stand, covered, for an additional 5 minutes.\'a0 Fluff with fork when ready to serve.\
\
Enjoy!}